The paper discusses the predictability of success in complex social systems using online social and information network data, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-categories of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Social and Behavioral Sciences (cs.SD), and Sociology (cs.SOC). The paper also uses models and simulations to explore the limits of predictability, which could place it in the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Cybersecurity (cs.CYBER).
